Dear Administrative Court Office,

Re: Zahmoul v Secretary of State for Justice & HMCTS
Administrative Court reference: AC-2025-LON-004293

I write to file a short Supplemental Note (for the record only) concerning =
the custodial handling of electronic devices seized and retained pursuant to=
 court process (=E2=80=9CImerman devices=E2=80=9D), as referred to at Grounds 3 and 4 of=
 the Amended Grounds of Claim dated 2 January 2026.

The Supplemental Note is filed for the limited purpose of placing recent co=
rrespondence on the court record which evidences the continued absence of an=
y identifiable administrative audit trail, custodial decision, or lawful han=
dling process in respect of court-controlled evidential material.

The Claimant does not invite the Court at this stage to determine the subst=
ance of any criminal allegations. The material is relied upon solely to pres=
erve the public-law record concerning evidential integrity, accountability, =
and court administration.

I attach:
Claimant=E2=80=99s Supplemental Note =E2=80=93 Custodial Handling of Imerman Devices (F=
or the Record)
Exhibit =E2=80=93 Claimant=E2=80=99s letter to Hughes Fowler Carruthers LLP dated 12 Ja=
nuary 2026
This email and the attached documents are copied to the Defendants by way o=
f service.

Yours faithfully,

Nadia Zahmoul
Claimant (Litigant in Person)

Copied to the Justice Committee for information.

=20

=20

=20

---------------------------------------------------------------------------=
---------------------------------------------

Nadia Zahmoul =20

Claimant =E2=80=94 Zahmoul v Secretary of State for Justice & HMCTS =20

High Court (Administrative Court) | Case Ref: AC-2025-LON-004293 =20

